  ;----------------------------------------------------------------------------
  ;Maximum Descriptor Sizes
  ;NOTE: MaxDescriptorSize must be big enough to include all Config,
  ;        Interface, End-Point, and any Class-specific Descriptors
  ;        that may be included with any multiple-interface Device.
  ;      Audio and Video Interface Devices, for example, generally
  ;        include an HID Interface to further "describe" the Device.
  ;        Since we don't know ahead of time whether the HID Interface
  ;        is a Joystick/GamePad or not (and it usually isn't with
  ;        and Audio or Video Interface Device), we have to download
  ;        the entire set of Descriptors and decipher them before
  ;        we can tell whether we should control it or not.
  ;      The Descriptor sizes for Audio and Video Interface devices
  ;        are usually VERY long, much longer than "normal" devices.
  ;        The standard "Get Configuration" Request downloads all of
  ;        the Class-specific Descriptors in addition to the general
  ;        Descriptors, and Audio and Video Interface Devices can have
  ;        a LOT of Class-Specific Descriptors.
  ;      I wish the designers of the Audio and Video Interface Specs
  ;        would have done what the HID designers did, and didn't
  ;        include ALL of the Class-specific data along with the general
  ;        Device data.
  ;----------------------------------------------------------------------------
  MaxDescriptorSize EQU 800 ;Max size of Device/Config/HID Descriptor
  MaxReportSize     EQU 600 ;Max size of Report Descriptor

  ;----------------------------------------------------------------------------
  ;USB Descriptor Types
  ;----------------------------------------------------------------------------
  DescrTypeDevice    EQU 01h ;Device
